As we stated earlier, Kotlin doesn’t let you use a generic type without specifying type arguments. Thus you may wonder how
         to check that the value is a list, rather than a set or another object. You can do that by using the special star projection syntax:


      if (value is List<*>) { ... }

people.filter(fun (person): Boolean {
